# 4
:::

::: {#fig-m3-dq layout-nrow="2"}

![Spawning Biomass Ratio](/Scenarios/plots_m3_plain/compare4_Bratio_uncertainty.png){#fig-m3-ratio}

![Spawning Biomass](/Scenarios/plots_m3_plain/compare2_spawnbio_uncertainty.png){#fig-m3-ssb}

![Fishing Mortality](/Scenarios/plots_m3/compare8_Fvalue_uncertainty.png){#fig-m3-f}

![Recruitment](/Scenarios/plots_m3_plain/compare10_recruits_uncertainty.png){#fig-m3-recruits}

Puerto Rico Yellowtail Snapper derived quantity time series across model scenarios (a_m3, v01_m3, v08_m3, v19_m3, v31_m3). Derived quantities plotted over time for (a) the relative spawning stock biomass (total biomass / virgin spawning stock biomass), (b) spawning stock biomass in thousands of metric tons, (c) fishing mortality (total biomass killed / total biomass), (d) and recruitment in millions of fish. The shaded areas and vertical bars in the derived quantities time series represent 95% confidence intervals. The values plotted prior to the model start year of 2012 reflect the unfished conditions and associated 95% confidence intervals.

# 9

::: {#fig-lenfit layout-ncol="3"}

![Model a_m3](/Scenarios/84_pr_f3_3cm_0648_0056_a_m3/plots/comp_lenfit__aggregated_across_time.png)

![Model v01_m3](/Scenarios/84_pr_f3_3cm_0648_0056_v01_m3/plots/comp_lenfit__aggregated_across_time.png)

![Model v08_m3](/Scenarios/84_pr_f3_3cm_0648_0056_v08a_m3/plots/comp_lenfit__aggregated_across_time.png)

![Model v19_m3](/Scenarios/84_pr_f3_3cm_0648_0056_v19a_m3/plots/comp_lenfit__aggregated_across_time.png)

![Model v31_m3](/Scenarios/84_pr_f3_3cm_0648_0056_v31a_m3_f2_0310/plots/comp_lenfit__aggregated_across_time.png)

Puerto Rico Yellowtail Snapper observed and predicted length distributions in centimeters aggregated across years for the Commercial (TIP) and National Coral Reef Monitoring Survey (NCRMP) length composition across model scenarios (a_m3, v01_m3, v08_m3, v19_m3, v31_m3). Green lines represent predicted length compositions, while gray regions represent observed length compositions. The effective sample sizes used to weight the length composition data are provided by N adj (the input sample size) and N eff (the calculated effective sample size) and are shown in the upper right corners. Model scenarios a_m3, v01_m3, and 08_m3 do not estimate recruitment deviations, while model scenarios v19_m3 and v31_m3 do. Super years are utilized for the commercial fleet in scenarios a_m3, v01_m3, v08_m3, and v19_m3 and for the national coral reef monitoring survey in scenario a_m3.

:::

Super years are utilized for the commercial fleet in scenarios a_m3, v01_m3, v08_m3, and v19_m3 and for the national coral reef monitoring survey in scenario a_m3.

Puerto Rico Yellowtail Snapper retrospective analysis of fecundity conducted by refitting models after removing five years of observation, one year at a time sequentially. Mohn's rho statistics and the corresponding "hindcast rho" measure the severity of retrospective patterns. The reference models (Ref) include the full time series ending in 2022. One-year-ahead projections are denoted by color-coded dashed lines with terminal points. Grey shaded areas are the 95% confidence intervals.
